org.hps.monitoring.ecal.eventdisplay.util

Class EcalWiringManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hps.monitoring.ecal.eventdisplay.util.EcalWiringManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<CrystalDataSet>

    public class EcalWiringManager
extends Object
implements Iterable<CrystalDataSet>
    Class EcalWiringManager reads in the crystal hardware data sheet for the calorimeter and stores the data in CrystalDataSet objects for access and reference by the Viewer classes. Crystal LCSim indices are mapped to the data set that corresponds to that crystal.

    • Constructor Detail

      • EcalWiringManager

        public EcalWiringManager(String dataFile)
                  throws IOException
        Initializes an EcalWiringManager database with hardware information loaded from the indicated file. The data file is assumed to be comma delimited and the first line is assumed to be a header line and to not contain data.
        Parameters:
        dataFile - - The path to the data file.
        Throws:
        IOException - Occurs if there is an error opening or parsing the data file.

      • EcalWiringManager

        public EcalWiringManager(String dataFile,
                         int delimiter,
                         boolean skipFirstLine)
                  throws IOException
        Initializes an EcalWiringManager database with hardware information loaded from the indicated file.
        Parameters:
        dataFile - - The path to the data file.
        delimiter - - The delimiter used by the data file.
        skipFirstLine - - Whether the first line should be skipped.
        Throws:
        IOException - Occurs if there is an error opening or parsing the data file.

    • Method Detail

      • getCrystalData

        public CrystalDataSet getCrystalData(Point crystalIndex)
        Gets the set of calorimeter hardware data associated with the crystal at the given index.
        Parameters:
        crystalIndex - - The index of the crystal for which to obtain the hardware information. This should be in LCSim coordinates.
        Returns:
        Returns the hardware information for the crystal as a CrystalDataSet object or returns null if the crystal index is invalid.

      • getFilteredCrystalList

        public List<Point> getFilteredCrystalList(Comparator<CrystalDataSet> conditions)
        Generates a list of all the crystals that match the conditions set in the argument Comparator object.
        Parameters:
        conditions - - An object defining the conditions that denote a "matched" crystal.
        Returns:
        Returns Point objects that contain the LCSim coordinates of all the crystals that produce a result of true with the method comparator.equals(crystal) .
